This article describes the '''localization''' (abbreviated '''L10N''') and '''internationalization''' (abbreviated '''I18N''') of software.

== System ==

=== Locale ===
{{InfoBox stack
|{{InfoBox wikipedia|Locale|header=true}}
}}
The locale defines your language, country and any special variant preferences. You find possible locales in {{Path|/usr/share/locale}}. E.g. for Germany choose ''<code>de-DE.UTF-8</code>''. A UTF-8 based locale is strongly recommended.

==== Kernel ====
You need to activate the following kernel options:
{{Kernel||<pre>
File Systems -->
  Native Language Support -->
    (utf8) Default NLS Option
    <*> NLS UTF8
</pre>}}

==== Generate locales ====
Add your locales to {{Path|/etc/locale.gen}} (optional: delete all other locales):
{{File|/etc/locale.gen||<pre>
de_DE.UTF-8 UTF-8
</pre>}}
Afterwards run '''locale-gen''' to generate the locales. '''locale -a''' lists all installed locales.

==== Use locales ====
Use '''eselect locale''' or manually add your locale to {{Path|/etc/env.d/02locale}} so the system uses the locale:
{{File|/etc/env.d/02locale||<pre>
LANG="de_DE.UTF-8"
LC_COLLATE="C"
</pre>}}

To apply the changes run:
{{RootCmd
|env-update
|source /etc/profile
}}

'''locale''' now shows your locale.

==== USE flag ====
Portage knows the global USE flag ''nls'' for enabling support for localization in other packages (default for almost all [[profile]]s). Also set the ''Linguas'' variable to only support only your language, e.g. for German:
{{File|/etc/portage/make.conf||<pre>
USE="... nls ..."
LINGUAS="de de_DE"
</pre>}}

After setting this you want to update your system so the changes take effect:
{{RootCmd|emerge --ask --changed-use --deep world}}

=== Console font ===
Change your {{Path|/etc/conf.d/consolefont}}, e.g. for German:
{{File|/etc/conf.d/consolefont||<pre>
CONSOLEFONT="lat0-16"
CONSOLETRANSLATION="8859-15_to_uni"
</pre>}}

=== Keyboard layout ===
Change your {{Path|/etc/conf.d/keymaps}}, e.g. for German:
{{File|/etc/conf.d/keymaps||<pre>
KEYMAP="de-latin1"
</pre>}}

=== Timezone ===
Set your timezone, e.g. for Germany:
{{RootCmd|cp /usr/share/zoneinfo/Europe/Berlin /etc/localtime}}

Change your {{Path|/etc/timezone}} to the same timezone:
{{File|/etc/timezone||<pre>
Europe/Berlin
</pre>}}

